Now, when I try to take a racecar, it seems to be broken, no matter how many races I did. There are also planes, with a note that there are questions the player can answer only. First and second place prizes apparently give blueprints.

Does anybody have an idea what's going on?

Currently, cars and planes have a priority of

First Place - Use directly (first of them) for free

Second Place - Fill up remaining of car or plane slots

Third and up place - platform specific stocks (Blueprints except planes) of those players who finished at the correct positions.

Both players and bots may obtain platforms here

Platform lists are usually (but not all the time) the same as the rewards from platform races. So have a look at the platform's other prizes to fill the remaining slots.

Platform cars and planes are only obtainable via their platform's stock! You need between 300 and 666 for a car/plan, with low tier being in the 300 range and high tiers in the 600-660ish range. You can also look at the platform's rating for a rough estimate of which platform has which tier for a race.

Go talk to the Cookie Monster in the Backflip Lounge and you may be able to help with getting these.
